caption: Bad: 1. sandwich construction was "slap-dash" at best. 2. You forgot to give me my drink and I was annoyed about my debit card not working and having to use my credit card and forgot all about it until I got back to work and realized I was never handed a cup. So I paid 2.99 for a tiny bag of chips. 3. Your service was slow and inefficient. 4. No napkins or spoons provided; hard to eat soup without a spoon. 5. I asked for my sandwich to be lightly toasted. This was NOT lightly toasted.  I am so unimpressed. The only redeeming factor is, the food tasted, ultimately good. However, I do not believe it was worth the $13 I paid for it.  Shame... You are so close to my job. Eating there frequently would have been so convenient.

They need new management period, other orders was neglected because they had a $200 dollars order they wanted to get out themselves and complained the order I was picking up was to big and had to wait for other order to be made, along with the line of people that came in, then they decided to work on the order by then the customer called and cancelled and they cost me money and time. Close or find some new worker, it was mainly the manager and her attitude about the order and stressing how their order was more important because it costed more. On 3 consecutive delivery orders the food has not been delivered at the requested order time.  For each order, I've called the shop 30 min after the expected delivery time and been told that the delivery company (Doordash) has not sent anyone to pick up and deliver my order.  For 2 of these orders, the manager has ended up personally delivering my food about 1.5 hrs after the expected delivery.  While I appreciate this gesture, something is inherently wrong with the delivery model.  Fool me 3x and shame on me.  I won't be ordering delivery from here again.

I mentioned I had went through the drive through twice but no one acknowledged it and she didn't even respond. Then, it seemed like 3 people came from the back and started helping the guy out. I eat at Potbelly’s all the time and the food is alway good. This location is close to my job. On 01/23/2020, I experienced the worst customer service. The worker Mario, was so disgusting and degrading. I was treated so badly I threw my food away. I couldn’t trust the quality of the food after dealing with such a nasty human being.  The GM was there the entire time and he did nothing. One of the workers, a young black lady, apologized for her co workers behavior. She should be the GM. I spoke to the assistant manger and they offered to give me lunch on them. I was going to accept it so I could give it to a person less fortunate but I would never feed someone something that I wouldn’t eat myself. I would never eat at a potbelly's again.

I generally like Potbelly's but this particular store at 545 West Madison was terrible. The sandwich maker got my order all wrong in spite of asking the standard questions and my clear answers to all, simply because he was too busy talking to a coworker and complaint about his break time or something. He even stopped making my sandwich, while I stood there waiting so he could finish his rant. Then the person at the register apparently didn’t know how to operate it, so she had to get some training from the manager, again while I’m standing there waiting with other customers behind me. My all-wrong sandwich wasn’t even warm after I made it through that cluster... I’m generally pretty patient and forgiving of little things, but this was ridiculous. Will not be back, at least at this location.
My sandwich was delicious!

I have to say I'm getting a bit tired of this place. First off I'll start by saying the sandwiches are good. You can customize your sandwich by what you tell the employee what you want on your sandwich. Here in lies the rub. This is probably the third time (that I can remember) I've had or heard of various problems. This last time was the last straw for me. It's when an employee argues with you about what you ordered vs what they thought you ordered. I always order the exact same thing so why would I switch it up and say something different? Well I didn't. Here's a tip for all managers, teach your employees to apologize and remake the sandwich. Period. NOT argue with the customer. What's the point of an employee arguing with a customer? There is no point! Remember, if you upset customers they go elsewhere (and there are alot of other places in the area) and they talk and tell their friends of their bad experience. I know it sucks and sometimes as an employee you really just want to tell a customer off but it's not worth it and if the manager is worth anything they will retrain that employee or get rid of them if they can't seem to get it through their head what the service industry is all about. And after hearing another employee at the same potbellys tell a different customer they were wrong I knew it wasn't just me. I will be going somewhere else.

My wife and I eat here on a regular basis for lunch during the week. The service is prompt, employees nice, and quality of food above par. I like the ‘live hippy music’ they bring in on occasion, as it helps to solidify the ‘hippy’ brand associated with Potbelly overall. I do wish that they would continue with this dogmatic approach and implement a recycling program, for much of what is thrown in the garbage, could be sent out for processing.
